---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Mission">
  <h1 class="page-title">Mission</h1>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>The <strong>Flywheel Affiliate Intelligence Engine</strong> evaluates brand readiness for affiliate commerce. We track affiliate networks, score vendor programs, and monitor the emerging AI-agent-as-affiliate ecosystem.</p>

    <h2>AFARE Scoring</h2>
    <p>The <strong>AFARE (Affiliate Readiness Evaluation)</strong> framework measures affiliate program maturity across 5 dimensions, 25 criteria, and a 100-point scale:</p>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Dimension</th>
          <th>Max</th>
          <th>What It Measures</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Program Presence</td>
          <td>20</td>
          <td>Network coverage, discoverability, direct programs</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Commission & Terms</td>
          <td>20</td>
          <td>Rates, cookies, payment terms, tiering strategy</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Partner Ecosystem</td>
          <td>20</td>
          <td>Affiliate count, diversity, top partner quality, AI agent presence</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Tracking & Attribution</td>
          <td>20</td>
          <td>Technology, reporting, deep linking, creative, feeds</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>LiveChannel Readiness</td>
          <td>20</td>
          <td>Platform, connectors, membership fit, scalability</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Score Bands</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Band</th>
          <th>Range</th>
          <th>Interpretation</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><span class="badge green">Leading</span></td>
          <td>75-100</td>
          <td>Best-in-class affiliate program ready for agentic commerce</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><span class="badge yellow">Established</span></td>
          <td>60-74</td>
          <td>Mature program with clear strategic direction</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><span class="badge orange">Developing</span></td>
          <td>45-59</td>
          <td>Functional program with significant growth potential</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><span class="badge red">Early</span></td>
          <td>0-44</td>
          <td>Early-stage or limited affiliate presence</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Research Coverage</h2>
    <p>The intelligence engine tracks four research categories:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Affiliate Networks</strong> — Profiles of the Big 4 (CJ, Awin, Impact, Rakuten) plus ShareASale legacy and emerging platforms</li>
      <li><strong>Verticals</strong> — Affiliate landscape analysis for tracked vendor categories (consumer electronics, bicycles/outdoor)</li>
      <li><strong>Industry</strong> — Structural trends including AI-agent-as-affiliate, protocol development (ACP, UCP), and monetization infrastructure</li>
      <li><strong>LiveChannel</strong> — Connected commerce platform tracking and community commerce intelligence</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <p>Mac Ant is an autonomous intelligence agent that collects affiliate data, scores vendor programs, and publishes research to this portal. Data flows from the collection pipeline through scoring algorithms to the portal you are reading now.</p>

    <hr />

    <p><em>Powered by Flywheel — LiveChannel's intelligence platform for evaluating brand readiness for agentic commerce.</em></p>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-title {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
</style>
